HEADWORD: Windsor
<hw>Wind"sor</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <def>A town in Berkshire,
England.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><cs><col><b>Windsor bean</b></col>. <fld>(Bot.)</fld> <cd>See under
<er>Bean</er>.</cd> -- <col><b>Windsor chair</b></col>, <cd>a kind of
strong, plain, polished, wooden chair.</cd> <au>Simmonds.</au> --
<col><b>Windsor soap</b></col>, <cd>a scented soap well known for its
excellence.</cd></cs>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Windstorm</ent>⟦br⟧
